Level 0: Scattered      -> 'new' in 10 files (worst)
Level 1: Simple Factory -> 'new' in 1 class
Level 2: Registry       -> 'new' in a Map (Supplier)
Level 3: Spring DI      -> 'new' in @Configuration
Level 4: External YAML  -> 'new' driven by config file (best)

// Each level pushes 'new' further from business logic.
// Zero coupling is IMPOSSIBLE in OOP -- someone must call 'new'.
